  "prompt": "What is the monthly income like for a sweetlegs distributor?",
  "response": "The monthly income for a Sweetlegs distributor can vary widely based on several factors, including individual sales performance, the size of their customer base, marketing efforts, and whether they participate in team building and recruitment. \n\nSweetlegs, a company that primarily sells women's leggings, operates on a direct sales model. Distributors earn commission on their personal sales and can also earn additional income by recruiting and building a team. Some distributors may only make a few hundred dollars per month, while others who are more successful or have built a larger team may earn significantly more.\n\nIf you're considering becoming a distributor, it's a good idea to reach out directly to current distributors or check for company-specific resources that may provide insights into potential earnings.",
